Carnivore grounds was the venue for the inaugural Mr and Miss Albinism Kenya beauty pageant held on Friday evening. The event was the first of its kind in Africa and celebrated people living with albinism. Present were Deputy President William Ruto, EAC cabinet secretary Phyllis Kandie, Albinism Society of Kenya founder Alex Munyere, nominated MP Isaac Mwaura and Kenya Film Classification Board CEO Ezekiel Mutua.